CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Saved From Possibly Death - Arrow points to heavily thicketed ravine near Leech Farm Veterans Hospital, Penn Township (above), where Mrs. Susie Tinsley was found by police, after being lost for two nights and a day... -Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Four men, including one in center wearing hat and dark jacket, standing in ravine near Leech Farm Veterans Hospital, Penn Township
